content: Placeholder for meeting in ~50 minutes
@T-release meeting!
@DPC triage checkin?
nm to report, going through report and closing a few inactive ones
ok
@XAMPPRocky I don't think I saw you file any issues after last week's discussion -- was there more you wanted to discuss there?
Yeah, I’ve been real busy (just started a new job) I’ll file the issue this weekend, but I had nothing about this last release specifically.
Ok, sounds good. Congratulations :)
In that case, there are no nominated issues that I think we need to discuss this time around.
There are a few stable-nominated PRs, but I don't think they need discussion.
(https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/77716 is the only one we have not discussed, and it has not yet been merged -- and may not be on a path to merging).
agenda is also empty, so let's @triagebot end-meeting to see if someone wants to talk about something

Does anyone have something to bring up?
React with :working_on_it: if you have something to say.
React with :all_good: if you're ready to end the meeting.

oh, one other heads up I wanted to make is that 1.49 is scheduled for december 31st. I think that should be fine personally but folks should be aware :) This is the next next release, current nightly.
I probably won't be available for that
Irrelevant fun fact, 0x31 is 49
I think it'll be my turn and I can do it

we can discuss more closer to the date -- in particular, if beta crater shows really poor results we might need to skip/move that release since fixing those around the holidays will be quite hard I imagine
I might try to queue a nightly crater later in the cycle for that reason.
ok, sounds like there's nothing else, so let's call the meeting here -- thanks all!
Later? Seems like that warrants doing stuff early
@cuviper we're in beta=1.48 right now
Oh, you mean late nightly as a pre-beta
so we've had very little 1.49 commits land
Ok
